Monocle2 Compatibility Patch (R4.3 Environment)
===============================================

SUMMARY
--------

This repository contains a patched version of Monocle2 (v2.9.0) that enables
stable execution under modern R environments. The original Monocle2 codebase
was written around 2016–2017 and assumes older versions of several core
packages such as Matrix, dplyr, igraph, and BiocGenerics.

In modern environments (e.g., R ≥ 4.0), multiple API changes lead to runtime
errors such as:

    Error: the condition has length > 1
    could not find function "clusterApply"
    unused argument (neimode = ...)
    group_by_ is deprecated

This patch resolves compatibility issues required for running Monocle2 under:

    R 4.3
    dplyr 1.1+
    Matrix 1.5+
    Bioconductor 3.18

Note that Monocle2 is NOT fully compatible with newer igraph APIs.
For maximum stability, igraph 1.2.11 is recommended.


Root Cause
----------

Most compatibility issues arise from major API changes in several core R
packages:

1. Matrix ≥ 1.5 changed sparse matrix class hierarchies.
2. dplyr ≥ 1.0 removed scoped functions such as group_by_() and select_().
3. BiocGenerics removed several parallel helper functions.
4. igraph ≥ 1.3 modified traversal APIs used by Monocle2.


Compatibility Fixes
-------------------

1. dplyr deprecated function: group_by_()

Original code:

    dplyr::group_by_(
        dplyr::select_(rownames_to_column(pData(cds)), "rowname", .dots=model_terms),
        .dots=model_terms
    )

Updated code:

    rownames_to_column(pData(cds)) %>%
        dplyr::select(rowname, dplyr::all_of(model_terms)) %>%
        dplyr::group_by(dplyr::across(dplyr::all_of(model_terms)))


2. dplyr deprecated function: select_()

Original code:

    dplyr::select_(rownames_to_column(pData(cds)), "rowname")

Updated code:

    rownames_to_column(pData(cds)) %>%
        dplyr::select(rowname)


3. dplyr do() environment variable bug

Original code:

    cds[, rowname]

Updated code:

    cds[, .$rowname]


4. BiocGenerics parallel functions removed

Original code:

    clusterApply(cl = cl, x = splitRows(x, length(cl)), ...)

Updated code:

    parallel::clusterApply(cl = cl, x = splitRows(x, length(cl)), ...)

Original code:

    clusterCall(cl, function(pkgs) {...})

Updated code:

    parallel::clusterCall(cl, function(pkgs) {...})

Original code:

    parRapply
    parCapply

Updated code:

    parallel::parRapply
    parallel::parCapply


Remove from NAMESPACE:

    importFrom(BiocGenerics,clusterApply)
    importFrom(BiocGenerics,clusterCall)
    importFrom(BiocGenerics,parCapply)
    importFrom(BiocGenerics,parRapply)


5. igraph traversal API change

Monocle2 uses the old igraph traversal API.

Original code:

    graph.dfs(dp_mst, root = root_cell, neimode = "all",
              unreachable = FALSE, father = TRUE)

Updated code:

    igraph::dfs(dp_mst, root = root_cell, mode = "all",
                unreachable = FALSE, parent = TRUE)

However, because several other igraph functions used internally by Monocle2
have also changed behavior in newer releases, the recommended igraph version
remains:

    igraph 1.2.11


6. class() logical vector bug (projection)

Original code:

    if(class(projection) != 'matrix')
        projection <- as.matrix(projection)

Updated code:

    if(!is.matrix(projection))
        projection <- as.matrix(projection)


7. tidyselect / rlang sym() compatibility bug

Original code:

    select(prin_graph_dim_1 = !!sym(x),
           prin_graph_dim_2 = !!sym(y))

Updated code:

    df <- as.data.frame(Matrix::t(reduced_dim_coords))

    df <- data.frame(
        prin_graph_dim_1 = df[,x],
        prin_graph_dim_2 = df[,y]
    )


8. branchTest progenitor_method bug

Original code:

    if (progenitor_method == "duplicate") {

Updated code:

    if (progenitor_method[1] == "duplicate") {


9. newCellDataSet class(cellData) bug

Original code:

    if (class(cellData) != "matrix" && isSparseMatrix(cellData) == FALSE)

Updated code:

    if (!is.matrix(cellData) && !isSparseMatrix(cellData))


10. Sparse matrix detection update

Original implementation:

    isSparseMatrix <- function(x){
        class(x) %in% c("dgCMatrix", "dgTMatrix")
    }

Updated implementation:

    isSparseMatrix <- function(x){
        inherits(x, "sparseMatrix")
    }


Tested Environment
------------------

This patched version was tested under the following environment:

    R              4.3
    monocle        2.9.0 (patched)
    Matrix         1.6-5
    Biobase        2.62.0
    VGAM           1.1-14
    DDRTree        0.1.5
    igraph         1.2.11
    ggplot2        4.0.2
    dplyr          1.2.0


Additional packages used during testing:

    plyr
    cluster
    fastICA
    irlba
    matrixStats
    densityClust
    Rtsne
    reshape2
    limma
    tibble
    qlcMatrix
    pheatmap
    stringr
    proxy
    slam
    viridis
    RANN
    Rcpp


Installation
------------

After applying the patches:

    R CMD INSTALL .

Restart R:

    .rs.restartR()
    library(monocle)


Supported Functions After Patch
-------------------------------

The patched version supports the full Monocle2 workflow:

    DDRTree
    orderCells
    plot_cell_trajectory
    BEAM
    branch heatmap
    differentialGeneTest


Recommended Distribution
------------------------

It is recommended to maintain a patched package directory:

    monocle_R43_fixed

Future installations can be done using:

    R CMD INSTALL monocle_R43_fixed
